### Custom REST API + GraphQL tests

@host = http://localhost:8080
@context = /PaolaRestApi_war_exploded
@base = {{host}}{{context}}/api/restapi

### 0) Check active source switch (LOCAL or PUBLIC)
GET {{base}}/switch
Accept: application/json

###

### 1) Get users (source-aware)
GET {{base}}/users
Accept: application/json

###

### 2) Get user by id (source-aware)
GET {{base}}/users/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 3) Create user (requires full-access bearer token from weather login)
@fullAccessToken = PASTE_FULL_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
POST {{base}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{fullAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "local.user@example.com",
  "first_name": "Local",
  "last_name": "User",
  "avatar": "https://reqres.in/img/faces/10-image.jpg"
}

###

### 4) Update user (requires full-access bearer token)
PUT {{base}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{fullAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "updated.local@example.com",
  "first_name": "Updated",
  "last_name": "User",
  "avatar": "https://reqres.in/img/faces/11-image.jpg"
}

###

### 5) Delete user (requires full-access bearer token)
DELETE {{base}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{fullAccessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 6) GraphQL users query (read)
POST {{base}}/graphql
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "query { users { id email first_name last_name avatar } }"
}

###

### 7) GraphQL updateUser mutation (requires full-access bearer token)
POST {{base}}/graphql
Authorization: Bearer {{fullAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "query": "mutation { updateUser }",
  "variables": {
    "id": 1,
    "email": "graphql.updated@example.com",
    "first_name": "Graph",
    "last_name": "QL",
    "avatar": "https://reqres.in/img/faces/12-image.jpg"
  }
}
